      "seed": 1422055216,
      "version": 469,
      "versionNonce": 29632816,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779643930198,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "2.) Consumer Groups: Where pool of workers that divides those partitions among themselves. \nEg. if there are 6 partitions group and 3 workers then each worker can consume 2 partitions, but number of \ncosumers/workers cannot be more then partitions.",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "2.) Consumer Groups: Where pool of workers that divides those partitions among themselves. \nEg. if there are 6 partitions group and 3 workers then each worker can consume 2 partitions, but number of \ncosumers/workers cannot be more then partitions.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
